OL,4,Cvictims of Post Office scandal
OL,6,FThose who have already settled for
OL,7,Fless money will have their
OL,8,Fcompensation topped up to this level,
OL,9,Fwhile people can instead choose to
OL,10,Fhave their claims assessed as part of
OL,11,Fthe usual scheme process, in which
OL,12,Fthere is no limit to compensation.
OL,14,FThe new Horizon Convictions Redress
OL,15,FScheme, to be run by the Department
OL,16,Ffor Business and Trade, is to open for
OL,17,Fapplications to those who have had
OL,18,Ftheir convictions quashed "as soon as
OL,19,Fpossible" once the legislation has
OL,20,Fpassed.
